# Ultimate Grilled Chicken Sandwich

> Juicy grilled chicken topped with crispy bacon, creamy garlic aioli, avocado, fresh veggies, and a drizzle of hot honey on a toasted brioche bun. A hearty, flavorful sandwich perfect for any occasion. #chicken #american #grill #sandwich

- Mayonnaise | 1 cup | 
- Garlic | 3 cloves | 
- Mustard | Dijon, 1 tbsp | 
- Lemon | 1 tbsp | Juiced

Mix all aioli ingredients in a bowl until well combined. Cover and set aside.

- Chicken | Breast, 4 boneless, skinless (6-8 oz each | 
- Garlic Powder | 1 tsp | 
- Paprika | 1 tsp | 
- Salt | 1½ tsp | 
- Black Pepper | To taste | 
- Olive Oil | Extra light, As needed | 

Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Preheat grill to medium-high. Mix seasonings in a small bowl, rub chicken with oil, then coat with the seasoning mix on both sides.

Grill chicken for 4–7 minutes per side until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C). Remove and let rest for a few minutes.

- Hamburger Buns | Brioche | 

While chicken rests, lightly toast buns on the grill.

- Avocados | 2 | 
- Tomato | 1 large | 
- Lettuce |  | 
- Bacon | 8 slices | 
- Red Onion | ½ | 
- Dill Pickles | As desired | 
- Hot Honey | To taste | 

Spread aioli on the bottom bun. Place grilled chicken on top. Layer with avocado, tomato, lettuce, bacon, onion, and pickles. Drizzle with hot honey. Cap with top bun.

Serve immediately while warm and juicy.

While chicken cooks, prepare the bacon.
